# Example Application

## Overview
The example application is a Next.js app located in [example/](mdc:example/) that demonstrates how to use the Trash Kit packages.

## Key Files
- [example/app/layout.tsx](mdc:example/app/layout.tsx) - Root layout component
- [example/app/page.tsx](mdc:example/app/page.tsx) - Home page
- [example/package.json](mdc:example/package.json) - Example app configuration
- [example/next.config.ts](mdc:example/next.config.ts) - Next.js configuration

## Purpose
- Demonstrates package usage patterns
- Provides development environment for testing
- Shows integration examples
- Serves as documentation through code

## Development Guidelines
1. Keep examples simple and focused
2. Show best practices for package usage
3. Update examples when adding new features
4. Ensure examples work with latest package versions

## Dependencies
- Uses the workspace packages as dependencies
- Includes Next.js for the application framework
- Minimal external dependencies

## Build Process
- Uses Next.js build system
- Integrates with the monorepo build process
- Serves as a test environment for packages